{
  "stem": "24111.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we tried to find a way to go to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And contacts at that time were very, very limited.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whatever contact we had with Switzerland was broken off, because now we were in hiding.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had no way of getting messages.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We decided to follow him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We have to split up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Arnold Weineger, Edgar Asher, his sister, and me, and Chichibo, we came together with Joschko.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Joschko came out of the cloister, came to the farmers, and we had a little what is called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We talked about it and we decided we will to try to find a way to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We will try to find the possibility of sending money to buy the smugglers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we will give you the direction how to do it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And on one day we left, and we went to Milan.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Like I told you, on the way we were bombed in Reggio Emilia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The train was stopped on one side of the city.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had to walk to the other side of the city because the railway was just-- it was bombed out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The train couldn't continue.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And on the other side of the city they had another train waiting and we continued.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we finally made it to Milano.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And finally we made it to Como Chiasso.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In Como Chiasso Chichibo found out that by Varese, Ponte Tresa, there is a possibility to cross the River Tresa.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the River Tresa is quite a large river, perhaps 20, 30 feet wide.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But on one point there is an underwater dam.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "An underwater dam is stone construction where the top is perhaps three feet wide.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
